text:
for those viewers who didnt play the game(tho for sure everyone played it already. It's been out for 5 years now) who are wondering what happened in the end:
In the end, Miles was killed by the Murkoff's private military to silence him. No personal reasons, if people were to learn about the gruesome events inside the asylum, Murkoff is going to fall. Miles then became the new host of the Walrider, just like what Gura said and murdered everyone in the scene.


more stuffs to read :
Billy isn't technically the "walrider", the walrider is an invention that was never mastered by the murkoff industry, just like what the doctor said. Walrider is some kind of nanotechnology. Im not sure what's the real purpose of it but I guess it's like a war machine or something. Anyways, that mount massive asylum isnt really a normal asylum, as we can see in the game. The asylum is just a front to hide their underground research for walrider, which they use the patients as their test subject. For someone to be able to control the walrider, they have to had witnessed some weird and horrible stuffs, that's why test subjects, Billy for example, is put under a lucid nightmare(?) for him to be able to control the walrider. Who is Chris Walker? He's an ex-military dude. His mission is to kill anyone that's a candidate for being a test subject for walrider, seeing that it's not possible to fully control the thing, even with Billy.

I hope she plays Whistleblower and Outlast 2. Whistleblower will explain what happened before, during, and after the original game's events. Outlast 2 tho is a completely different story, somewhat connected, but not really.

text:
Ok gura you miss so much evidence on this game. Especially, "Record it" evidence video. Don't worry gura did nothing wrong right......
I'm gonna explain story of Outlast 1


Outlast 1: Mount Massive Asylum was once used for I forgot what but then it closed and a company called Murkoff bought it back. Now the main point is: Murkoff are the very bad guys. They are corporate people who values wealth over health if you know what I mean. And you know cause you've had the bad idea to go in there.
Now in the asylum you have: the big baddies (Doctor Tragger, Piggy Piggy Walker and so on) which were originally really fucked up ; and you have the random dudes called "Variants" (which technically also include the big guys) who are patients usually not evil initially but what Murkoff did transformed a bunch into killing machine (though note that I'd say 80% of the Variants never actually tried to kill you).
What did Murkoff you might ask? Simple enough: experimentations on humans. Classic. But their most beloved project? The Morphogenic Engine or The Billy Project you could say or the "F*cking Ghost Trying To Kill Me". They had this idea of nanotechnology who could, if I remember correctly, heal the body or something like that or at least make you very OP. And it would be mind-controlled through lucid dreaming kinda. But in order for someone to actually manage that, they had to witness enough horrors and survive thus we arrive to the Morphogenic Program which is the weird screen showing of those Shrink Pictures with the distorted sound.
Basically Murkoff re-opened the Asylum, got a bunch of "useless humans nobody cared about" or rather a bunch of guinea pigs, and they threw everyone into the machine (the bubble thingy at the end of the game) to search for the One.
The patients you see in the Asylum, the Variants, if they don't die due to the machine, they become significantly weirder as you saw and for some (the big guys) significantly more violent are they not?
Now you remember Billy Hope? Or the Wallrider? Or the Ghost maybe? Yeah, same person, he succeeded the experiment and was able to control the nanomachines. You lost? The ghost you see is not a ghost but a conglomerate of thousands of nanomachines flying in the air. Notice he cannot go through walls, he can surely crawl under tiny surfaces (beneath doors for example) but he's not a real ghost per say.
Now that's the big story I can explain the others like Father Martin and all if you want but boy would that take time üòÇ
Basically, Miles Upshur the player, goes in the Asylum, finds out about everything, shuts down the machine, kills Billy, and dies dramatically in the end.
Or did he?

Play a Outlast DLC "Whistleblower" = Prequel of Outlast
